    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-09-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="99" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-09-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 21, 1890</date>.
                            (City of Mexico, September 21, 1890.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Ryan states that a telegram from Minister Mizner asks him to telegraph
                        the Department that peace and order reign in Guatemala, and that his (Mr.
                        Mizner’s) next dispatch will conclude the history of the case of General
                        Barrundia.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
